Malignant: Malignant epithelial cells from prostate cancer, showing abnormal proliferation and cancer-specific gene expression patterns
Unassigned: Cells with unclear cell type assignment, may represent rare cell types or cells in transition states
Epithelial: Normal epithelial cells in prostate tissue, involved in prostate function and tissue structure
T_cell: T lymphocytes in prostate tissue, involved in adaptive immune response and immune surveillance
Endothelial: Endothelial cells lining blood vessels in prostate tissue, involved in vascular function and angiogenesis
Fibroblast: Fibroblast cells in prostate tissue, involved in extracellular matrix production and tissue remodeling
Macrophage: Macrophage immune cells in prostate tissue, involved in immune response and tissue homeostasis
Mast: Mast cells in prostate tissue, involved in inflammatory responses and immune regulation
B_cell: B lymphocytes in prostate tissue, involved in antibody production and humoral immune response
